## Vercel Web Analytics Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this TanStack Start (React/Vite) project.

### Changes Made

**Modified Files:**
1. `package.json` - Added `@vercel/analytics` dependency
2. `package-lock.json` - Updated lockfile with new dependencies
3. `src/routes/__root.tsx` - Added Analytics component to root layout

### Implementation Details

Following the latest official Vercel Analytics documentation (fetched from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart):

1. **Package Installation**: Installed `@vercel/analytics` package using npm
   - Package version: Latest version from npm registry

2. **Integration**: Added the Analytics component to the root layout
   - Imported `Analytics` from `@vercel/analytics/react` (React framework path)
   - Placed the `<Analytics />` component in the `RootShell` function, which renders the HTML structure
   - Positioned after `<Scripts />` inside the `<body>` tag, following React best practices

3. **Framework-Specific Implementation**: 
   - This is a TanStack Start project using Vite
   - Used the React integration path (`@vercel/analytics/react`)
   - Added to the root layout component (`__root.tsx`) which wraps all routes
   - The component will be rendered on every page of the application

### Verification

✅ Build completed successfully - no errors
✅ Linter ran without issues
✅ Analytics component properly bundled (visible in build output as `_libs/vercel__analytics.mjs`)

### Next Steps for Deployment

To activate analytics tracking:
1. Deploy this project to Vercel using `vercel deploy` or via Git integration
2. Navigate to the Analytics tab in your Vercel project dashboard
3. Click the "Enable" button to activate analytics
4. Data will start appearing in the dashboard once users visit your site

### Technical Notes

- The Analytics component is lightweight and doesn't impact page load performance
- It automatically tracks page views for all routes
- Analytics requests will be sent to `/_vercel/insights/*` paths after deployment
- The implementation follows Vercel's official guidelines for React/Vite projects
